Case (i) [latex]\mathbf{t} \lt 1[/latex] At steady state, capacitor behaves as open circuit and inductor behaves as short circuit. Redraw the circuit: Using current division, [latex]
\begin{aligned}
\mathrm{i}_{\mathrm{L}}\left(0^{-}\right) & =\frac{3}{3+2} \times 10=6 \mathrm{~A} \\
\therefore \quad \mathrm{V}_{\mathrm{C}}\left(0^{-}\right) & =5 \times 2=12 \mathrm{~V}
\end{aligned}
[/latex] Case (ii) [latex]\mathbf{t} \gt 0[/latex] : Switch is opened. [latex]\because \quad \mathrm{V}_{\mathrm{C}}\left(0^{-}\right)=\mathrm{V}_{\mathrm{C}}\left(0^{+}\right)=12 \mathrm{~V}[/latex] and [latex]\quad \mathrm{i}_{\mathrm{L}}\left(0^{-}\right)=\mathrm{i}_{\mathrm{L}}\left(0^{+}\right)=6 \mathrm{~A}[/latex] Redraw the circuit [latex]\mathrm{t}=0^{+}[/latex]: Apply KVL in loop, [latex]
\begin{array}{rlrl}
12+8-12-\mathrm{V}_{\mathrm{L}} & =0 \\
\Rightarrow & \mathrm{V}_{\mathrm{L}} & =8 \mathrm{~V}
